 university has to offer the walter h shorenstein fellow will focus on contemporary political economic or social change in the asia pacific region including northeast southeast and south asia or topics in international relations and international political economy the fellow will take part in center activities throughout the academic year and present their research findings in center seminars they will also participate in the center's publication program the fellowship is made possible through the generosity of walter h shorenstein shorenstein fellowships in contemporary asia fellowship for postdoctoral scholars professionals international scholars not accepting applications at this time search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest now accepting developing asia health policy fellowship applications january 25 2012 ahpp announcement shorenstein aparc welcomes new research fellows for 2010 2011 june 22 2010 announcement shorenstein aparc announces new fellowships and faculty searches for the 2010 2011 academic year september 9 2009 news shorenstein aparc announces new shorenstein fellows for 2008 09 march 16 2008 news shorenstein aparc invites applications for two new academic positions in japanese and korean studies july 29 2007 fsi stanford shorenstein aparc announcement aparc renamed the walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center september 20 2005 press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
